definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group.
An O-sulfoamino acid consisting of methyl L-tyrosinate in which the hydrogen of the phenolic hydroxy group has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A ketoaldonic acid comprising D-fuconic acid lacking the 3-hydroxy substituent and having a keto group at the 2-position.
